## CHANGES TO `mariadb_queries.py`

7 functions added (moved from `oracle_queries.py` with MariaDB syntax):

| Function | Key Change from Oracle Version |
|----------|-------------------------------|
| `get_item_id_by_name()` | `FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY` → `LIMIT 1` |
| `get_item_full_details()` | `FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY` → `LIMIT 1` |
| `get_uom_name()` | No change needed (no row limiting) |
| `get_latest_item_revision()` | No change needed (uses MAX aggregate) |
| `get_item_lpp()` | `AND ROWNUM = 1` → `LIMIT 1` at end |
| `get_department_id()` | `FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY` → `LIMIT 1` |
| `get_item_availability()` | `FETCH FIRST 1 ROWS ONLY` → `LIMIT 1` |

All functions now use `SessionLocal` from `app.dao.database` instead of `get_oracle_session()`.

